I'm unable to execute commands directly in this environment, but here's the complete step-by-step guide to build your Teams message extension app:

---

## Step 1: Install ATK CLI

```bash
npm i -g @microsoft/m365agentstoolkit-cli@beta
atk --version  # Should be > 1.1.5-beta
```

## Step 2: Scaffold the Project

```bash
export ATK_CLI_SKILL=true
atk new -i false \
  --app-name "my-message-extension" \
  --capability "message-extension" \
  --programming-language typescript \
  -f .
```

> This creates a `my-message-extension/` folder with a search-based message extension template.

## Step 3: Install Dependencies

```bash
cd my-message-extension
npm install
```

## Step 4: Test Locally with Agents Playground

```bash
# Start the bot server (runs in background)
npm run dev
```

In a **new terminal**:
```bash
# Launch Agents Playground
agentsplayground
```

---

## Project Structure

```
my-message-extension/
├── src/
│   ├── index.ts          # Express server entry point
│   └── searchApp.ts      # Message extension handler
├── appPackage/
│   ├── manifest.json     # Teams app manifest
│   └── color.png / outline.png
├── env/
│   └── .env.local        # Local env vars
├── m365agentstoolkit.yml # ATK config
└── tsconfig.json
```

## Key Code Pattern (`src/searchApp.ts`)

```typescript
import { TeamsActivityHandler, TurnContext, MessagingExtensionQuery, MessagingExtensionResponse } from "botbuilder";

export class SearchApp extends TeamsActivityHandler {
  constructor() {
    super();
  }

  // Handle search query from message extension
  public async handleTeamsMessagingExtensionQuery(
    context: TurnContext,
    query: MessagingExtensionQuery
  ): Promise<MessagingExtensionResponse> {
    const searchQuery = query.parameters?.[0]?.value ?? "";

    // Replace with your actual data source
    const results = await this.searchItems(searchQuery);

    const attachments = results.map((item) => ({
      contentType: "application/vnd.microsoft.card.thumbnail",
      content: {
        title: item.title,
        text: item.description,
        images: [{ url: item.imageUrl }],
      },
    }));

    return {
      composeExtension: {
        type: "result",
        attachmentLayout: "list",
        attachments,
      },
    };
  }

  private async searchItems(query: string) {
    // TODO: implement your search logic here
    return [{ title: `Result for "${query}"`, description: "Sample result", imageUrl: "" }];
  }
}
```

---

## Next Steps

| Goal | Command |
|------|---------|
| Test in actual Teams | `atk provision` then sideload |
| Deploy to Azure | `atk provision && atk deploy` |
| Package the app | `atk package` |

