## Build a Teams Message Extension (TypeScript)

### Step 1: Install ATK CLI

```bash
npm i -g @microsoft/m365agentstoolkit-cli@beta
atk --version   # should be > 1.1.5-beta
```

### Step 2: Scaffold the Project

```bash
export ATK_CLI_SKILL=true

atk new -i false \
  --capability message-extension \
  --programming-language TypeScript \
  --app-name my-message-extension \
  -f .
```

This scaffolds a **Search-based Message Extension** (most common). ATK supports these ME types:
| Type | `--capability` value |
|---|---|
| Search-based | `message-extension` |
| Action-based | `message-extension-action` |
| Link unfurling | `link-unfurling` |

### Step 3: Install Dependencies

```bash
cd my-message-extension
npm install
```

### Step 4: Test Locally (Agents Playground — no M365 needed)

```bash
atk provision --env local -i false
npm run dev
# In a new terminal:
npx agentsplayground
```

### Project Structure Overview

```
my-message-extension/
├── src/
│   ├── index.ts          # Express server entry point
│   ├── searchApp.ts      # Message extension handler
│   └── adaptiveCards/    # Card templates
├── appPackage/
│   ├── manifest.json     # Teams app manifest
│   └── color.png / outline.png
├── env/
│   └── .env.local        # Local environment variables
└── m365agentstoolkit.local.yml   # ATK config
```

### Key Code Pattern (Search Extension)

```typescript
// src/searchApp.ts
import { TeamsActivityHandler, TurnContext } from "botbuilder";
import { MessagingExtensionQuery, MessagingExtensionResponse } from "@microsoft/teams-js";

export class SearchApp extends TeamsActivityHandler {
  constructor() {
    super();
  }

  // Handle search query
  public async handleTeamsMessagingExtensionQuery(
    context: TurnContext,
    query: MessagingExtensionQuery
  ): Promise<MessagingExtensionResponse> {
    const searchQuery = query.parameters?.[0]?.value ?? "";

    // Fetch your data here
    const results = await this.searchItems(searchQuery);

    return {
      composeExtension: {
        type: "result",
        attachmentLayout: "list",
        attachments: results.map(item => ({
          contentType: "application/vnd.microsoft.card.thumbnail",
          content: {
            title: item.title,
            text: item.description,
          },
        })),
      },
    };
  }

  private async searchItems(query: string) {
    // Replace with your real data source
    return [{ title: `Result for: ${query}`, description: "Sample result" }];
  }
}
```

### Step 5: Deploy to Azure (when ready)

```bash
atk provision --env dev -i false
atk deploy --env dev -i false
```

---

**Which ME type are you building?** Search, action-based (form), or link unfurling? I can provide more specific code for your use case.

